## Description of change

- Adapters can provide a new method `paapiParameters`, which takes the same argument as `buildRequests`, and should return an object mapping arbitrary names to PAAPI asynchronous parameters (currently, auction nonces and B&A auction data).
- If paapi is enabled for a bidder, its `bidderRequest.paapi.createAuctionNonce` and `.getInterestGroupAdAuctionData` can be used to ask for the corresponding navigator APIs,
- the parameters are resolved and populated in `bidderRequest.paapi.params` before `buildPaapiConfigs` and `buildRequests`.

For example:

```javascript
registerBidder({
    paapiParameters(validBidRequests, bidderRequest) {
        return {
             nonce: bidderRequest.paapi.createAuctionNonce(),
             igData: bidderRequest.paapi.getInterestGroupAdAuctionData(...)
        }
    }, 
    buildPAAPIConfigs(validBidRequests, bidderRequest) {
         const {nonce, igData} = bidderRequest.paapi.params;
         // here (and in `buildRequests`) nonce and igData are resolved return values from those navigator APIs
    }
})
```

